casebody.data:
Second Department,

February, 1942.

(February 3, 1942.) In the Matter of the Application of Brooklyn Bar Association in Respect of Litchfield F. Moynahan, an Attorney and Counselor at Law, Respondent.

Proceeding to discipline an attorney. Motion to confirm report of official referee granted and respondent suspended from the practice of the law for a period of two years. Present — Lazansky, P. J., Hagarty, Carswell, Johnston and Adel, JJ.
